<img class="alignnone wp-image-248510 size-full" src="https://i1.wp.com/tooxclusive.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/image1.jpeg?resize=500%2C330&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="500" height="330" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Nigerian music producer; REXXIE has just been crowned  “African Producer of the year” at the SoundCity MVP Awards in Lagos, Nigeria. Rexxie beat the likes of Prince Kaybee (SA), S2Kizzy (TZ), MOG (GH), Cracker (NG), KelP (NG), Pheelz (NG), and Jaysynth (NG) to bag the prestigious award at the event that was held in January 11, 2020. Rexxie was quite overwhelmed about this victory and he had this to say on stage when he walked up to pick the award, “I want to say a big thank you to everyone, I wasn’t expecting this but God bless everybody, God bless my team, and my family!” This was Rexxie’s first major award nomination and it couldn’t have ended better for the prolific producer as he won the prestigious award at his first attempt. The producer has already kick-started the year 2020 with some amazing collaborations in the works with Images of a hit music session with Tiwa Savage and Naira Marley surfacing on the internet some days back. We can only hope for even more hits from the brain behind some of Nigeria’s biggest hits of 2019. The likes “Soapy” by Naira Marley, “Zanku” by Zlatan, DMW’s “Bum Bum” and a whole lot more. The post Rexxie Bags “African Producer Of The Year” Award Source: Too Xclusive Record release after record release, massive hit songs, absolutely amazing new revelations, record-shattering sales, globally sold-out concerts…the year 2019 has definitely been one of the most amazing ever witnessed in the African pop music scene. Now its time to recognize who are the real MVPs of the 2019 Afro-Pop Music… December 26, 2019 In "Music/Video" Lagos went on a standstill on Saturday, the 11th of January 11, 2020, as Soundcity rewarded artistes for their talents over the previous year at the Soundcity MVP Awards, an annual music awards that celebrate 